storyInfo: Zima is assigned to captain a Rhodes Island advance squad. At around this time, she announces a major decision to the other members of the Ursus Student Self-governing Group.

attributes.content: (Lada's... not here either?)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: (She sure has been busy lately.)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: C-Captain!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Hm? Oh, hey, Mousse.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You did nice in that last combat drill.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Heheh. I went through Leto's brutal training course, after all.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Huh? Rosalind?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Mm-hm! When the new squad rosters were posted, I saw you were my captain... I remembered the two of you were best friends, so I went and asked her how best to work with you in battle.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: She agreed to train with me straight away! And she taught me this little trick for when I fight alongside you...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: What's the trick?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: She said, 'If Sonya heads up, just head up with her!'
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: That dumbass... Grrr... I was wondering why I couldn't even find her. She was training with you, huh?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: No, not just me... there's been a lot of operators fighting for the chance to train with her.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: And the way it's been as of late, once she's in the training room, she spends the whole day there... *sigh* I wonder when I'll ever have energy as exuberant as her?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Jeez, you don't see that every day.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Operator A

attributes.content: I've never seen a newbie like that. Fresh transfer from Logistics to the front line, if you could believe it.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Operator A

attributes.content: Bored clean through a solid steel plate with that custom crossbow she's got... I'm sweating here!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Operator A

attributes.content: That's not even the scariest part... did you hear? Stormeye was talking up the newbie hard during combat drills. A first for him.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Operator B

attributes.content: (Is that Natalya they're talking about? No way.)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: (Not like that should be surprising. Weird. The hell am I feeling...?)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: (Shouldn't I be happy for her?)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: (Whatever, this sucks... Guess I'll take a look. Should just about be there.)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: (Is that voices from inside? Sounds like a lotta people...)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Huh? Is someone at the door?
Allow me, Royal Detective, to get to the bottom of this.
Z... Zima! I assume you're here for Istina?
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: She's... currently sharing her thoughts on A Winter Campfire with us! This book right here!
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: I'll bring her over!
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: W—Wait, no, no need...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Not like it's anything important. I'll just come back a little later.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: *huff*.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Five days later...
Maybe Rosalind's here?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Yeah, nope. Didn't think so.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Took me the whole morning just to fry one pirozhki. Still doesn't taste half as good as Lada's.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I went and borrowed A Winter Campfire from May. Should be able to finish reading it tonight.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: And that black tea still tastes so bad I wanna die... but I get it now. Natalya's been relying on that weird mouthfeel to stay awake the whole time!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Nowadays...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Life's simple... for us, the USSG. It should've been like this before, shouldn't it?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Uh... Nearl. You heard all that?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Whatever, perfect timing.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I'm not totally cool with the squad assignments. I think Istina, Leto and the rest would do better on a team with me.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Nearl

attributes.content: You... C'mon, you're messing around, right? We've always been a team.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Our squads at current are not based on whether its members come from the same place, or how deeply they know each other.
attributes.name: Nearl

attributes.content: It is Rhodes Island strategic necessity. You're bound for the battlefield.
attributes.name: Nearl

attributes.content: Our plans are made in the wake of the most responsible decisions, with full stock taken of our mission objectives, coupled with the best of every operator's individual abilities and team synergies.
attributes.name: Nearl

attributes.content: How come you never seem to get pissed off?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Zima, very soon you'll be leading a reorganized squad to carry out your mission.
attributes.name: Nearl

attributes.content: You must remember: here and now, you are a team captain.
attributes.name: Nearl

attributes.content: Hmph... yeah, I hear that. 'Captain.'
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: So that's my new title, huh?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Phew... oof, it gets real cold here at night...
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: Captain, you want a smoke? Warm yourself up?
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: I mean... I assume you're old enough?
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: I don't smoke.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Also, you wanna be careful.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Ursus gets real dry this time of year. One spark can catch the moment it hits grass.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Got it. Guess I won't smoke either.
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: Eesh... it's freezing... say, don't you guys think this mission's a little slow-going?
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: Do we really need this many hands looking for one shipment of lost meds?
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: I... I believe Nearl must have had strategical considerations in arranging for us to go!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: *sigh* Arrangements, my butt.
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: We're a bunch of rookies, we don't have any actual combat experience. What, are you hoping commander's about to send us on harder missions?
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: I'm just sad I didn't get put in the same squad as that one Medical girl I trained with. I was even gonna...
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: Wait! Guys, look...
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: There—There's fire that way!
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: C'mon. We're gonna check it out.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: O—Oh, jeez... this whole tent got burnt down...
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: Rhodes Island logo... this was one of our temp stations.
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: Are the airtight containers in there the missing medical supplies?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Anna, compare those with the designs for Medical's pharms.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Um... Captain, Istina's not in our squad...
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: Goddammit.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Captain, permission to speak freely, you've been kind of distracted this whole mission.
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: You, Istina and Rosa and the rest were one student group, right?
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: But we're a whole squad here. Didn't The Radiant Knight tell us to trust in our teammates out in the field?
attributes.name: Defender Operator

attributes.content: Um...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Captain, I've made a rough check. That should be the lost shipment in the tent.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's gotta be! The packaging's the exact same as the stuff awaiting transit on the landship.
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: Let's go, c'mon, everyone ease up! Let's bring the spoils of victory home... Who knew it'd be this easy!
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: Wa... Hey, wait!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Geugh...
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: Wh—Who are you guys? Get outta my way!
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: No more funny business!
attributes.name: Surly Bandit

attributes.content: Last one was your arm. The next one's aimed at your head if you try anything!
attributes.name: Surly Bandit

attributes.content: Who the hell are you people?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: No comment.
attributes.name: Indifferent Bandit

attributes.content: Drop your meds, your equipment, and any other valuables you have right here, and we'll let him go.
attributes.name: Indifferent Bandit

attributes.content: Bratany!
attributes.name: Indifferent Bandit

attributes.content: Captain...
attributes.name: Sniper Operator

attributes.content: Ugh.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Seanson, you hold steady.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Huh? Captain, don't do anything rash...
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Mousse! We're going in!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: R—Roger!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Gargh!
attributes.name: Surly Bandit

attributes.content: Ugh...
attributes.name: Indifferent Bandit

attributes.content: Hey, kid.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You're their boss, aren't you?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Speak!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: He's passed out.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Hmph. Guess he couldn't take a beating.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Seanson, you okay?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I'm surprised you remember my name, Captain.
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: It's okay, my wounds aren't deep... I can do some simple first-aid on myself...
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Swear my heart was about to leap out of my mouth, though.
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: I don't think I'm fit for the battlefield... I need to hand in an application to command later, see if I can't get transferred to Logistics or Medical.
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Coward.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Lucci, how are things in the tent?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I gave a search. Those supply boxes are definitely Rhodes Island's, without a doubt.
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: But they're all empty inside! The pharmaceuticals are gone!
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: Dammit! Wake up, you dumbass! Quit playing dead!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Zima seizes the bandit leader by the scruff and tosses him to and fro—vigorously enough to throw the goods in his pockets all across the floor.
Is... Is that... a Peterheim Middle School... student ID?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Where am I...?
attributes.name: Indifferent Bandit

attributes.content: Morning, bozo.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Y—You were in the forest... Where are we? What are you doing with me? Where are my bratany?
attributes.name: Indifferent Bandit

attributes.content: 20 Questions the second you wake up, huh? You're a pain in the ass.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: We brought you back, gave you a checkup, put you on energy supplements for your malnutrition, and got you permission to stay in a dorm. Feel free not to thank us, I guess, but—
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: At least show a little respect?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Daniil.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: How do you know my name...?
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: Your student ID.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Didn't think I'd run into a schoolmate in some crappy forest all the way out there.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You don't know me?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: General Zima? I didn't even recognize you.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: Alright, whatever, you remember me. That makes this a lot simpler.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I've got one question, that's it.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: The medical stuff. Where did it go?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I sold it.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: You sold it? Then where's the money?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: ...Spent it all.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: Are you serious?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You dickhead... If only I knew you'd pull this shit. Should've let those noble kids beat on you longer.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Okay. You sold it. So tell me about your buyer, your broker, and the amount of money your stolen goods got, and don't miss a single thing.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You need to understand—Rhodes Island might be housing you for now, but if you don't cooperate, we can just hand you over to the Ursus police.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I must be dreaming. General Zima using 'I'll sic the police on you' to threaten me... It looks like everyone's changed since Chernobog.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: General Zima... no, Sonya. I would've probably done as you told me if we were back in Peterheim.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: I had no choice there, after all. It was either follow you, or beg those noble shitstains for forgiveness as they kicked me about.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: Who says you can't follow me now? You'll be part of the USSG until whenever.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: This is Rhodes Island. It was Rhodes Island that sheltered us, and brought us out of Chernobog.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I don't actually know if you can join too... but I figure as long as you're wiling to work, it should be fine.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Hmph. The Ursus Student Self-governing Group, was it? What a nostalgic name.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: If Anna's here too, then why wasn't she with you out there? Those two bratany in your squad probably don't have half the brain cells combined that Anna did.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: Grr. Those are my squaddies. I won't have you talking shit about them.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: And Anna's... the group's got their own things to do.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Hmph, their own things. You weren't really thinking you could lead the USSG your whole life, were you?
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: If Rhodes Island is sheltering you, then they must have taken in Anna and the rest too.
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: So how could they have clung to your side forever, the way they were before?
attributes.name: Daniil

attributes.content: Ugh.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Of course they're not gonna be with me all the time, and that's for the best.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I never really planned for the future, anyway.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I used to think, if we all made it out of Chernobog... then no matter what the future brought, it couldn't be worse than that, could it?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Real talk, Rhodes Island is just fine to us now. We got used to life here, and we've all found our own thing to do.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: For me, Peterheim's in the past. Same for the USSG.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Five days ago...
H—Huh? Disband?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You want to disband the USSG?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I'mma sniff a sec... doesn't smell sweet... you're not honey-drunk.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Wait, what's this crazy talk, then?!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: It's not crazy talk. It's my official decision.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Sonya...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Natalya just got back. Didn't we agree to welcome her home together? To celebrate her achievements?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Even if you're of a mind to disband the USSG... now's not the time to bring that up, is it?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: No. Now's the perfect time.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Our group was founded on the idea that we'd support each other through those hellish days.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But now, we're out. All of us in the USSG have found stuff we'd rather put our energy into aboard Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Like Natalya has. She started out not knowing how to fight at all, now she's posting great scores in combat drills... She's the best out of all of us, the way she's changed.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I used to worry I wouldn't make a decent leader... Maybe I've earned your trust and support after so long.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But that doesn't mean I can hold onto my position forever.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I used to be the USSG's leader, now I'm the captain of a Rhodes Island advance squad... and there's more possibilities out there for Sonya's future.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: All of your futures.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Um—I—still don't really get it.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: How does it actually affect us if the Group disbands?
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Even if the USSG's gone, the five of us will still be together, right?
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Lada, this is different. Don't you wanna be a great chef? And Anna says she wants to go study at university.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: For our past selves, all of that was empty dreams. But now, we have better footing, and I think... no, I'm sure everyone's got a way better future in store.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: We're gonna be more than just members of the Ursus Student Self-governing Group. We're all gonna better ourselves.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Well, I'm lost for words. Hats off to our leader.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I certainly never expected... that the first to leave the Ursus Student Self-governing Group would be you, of all people.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: It's not just me leaving, it's the USSG disbanding! You're all free now!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Sonya.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Is that how you've decided to resolve our futures?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I mean... I assume you're old enough?
Urk...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: So how could they have clung to your side forever, the way they were before?
Urk...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: How does it actually affect us if the Group disbands?
Blughk—
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: She vomits, cleanly as could be.
Sonya, you know you're not omnipotent.
This is for the best for every single member of the USSG.

attributes.text: The water in the toilet basin becomes a whirlpool, like it's about to suck me in, pull me away from a life where they exist.
Right now, my future lies before me.

attributes.content: Seriously... I thought we'd get to rest up for a while.
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: All we had was a few days back on the landship, and now they sent us out to a place like this.
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: It's way colder than last time.
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: Plus our captain still acts like she's got it all to win... Just kill me.
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: You think? She looks to me like she's just forcing herself along.
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Actually, did you hear? That student group of theirs broke up!
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Huh? Is she for real?
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: What the hell are you two bitching about now?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Oh, Captain! No bitching here, none at all!
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Yeah, you're off the hook this time.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Lucci, pass me a smoke.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Captain, The Radiant Knight went out of her way to give me a warning.
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: I'm never gonna hand out smokes again. Don't hurt me for it.
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: Ugh. Screw you, Nearl, stepping into my business.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Oh, yeah, uh, Captain...
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Did Daniil really just tell you the village's location like that?
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: They hid that many medical supplies in this one village?
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: It was Nearl who told me... Literally no idea how she got it out of Daniil, though.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But she's always going around all like 'just leave it to me,' so I'm not that surprised.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But is there really going to be an inhabited village... in a place this desolate?
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: Captain, you don't think The Radiant Knight's testing you, do you...?
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: L—Look!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Over there, I think that's an old man.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: What could it be, youngster?
attributes.name: Old Man

attributes.content: Fresh faces are seldom sighted, out here in this tundra.
attributes.name: Old Man

attributes.content: Is there a village around here?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Do you see that hut over there? Go past it, and you'll find our village.
attributes.name: Old Man

attributes.content: You don't... uh, excuse me, but you wouldn't happen to know a Daniil, would you?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Daniil, eh...?
attributes.name: Old Man

attributes.content: Chi—Chief! Trouble!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: What is it?
attributes.name: Old Man

attributes.content: There's a fire in the village! It's about to reach the storehouse! All our food for the winter is in there!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: *pant*... *pant*... Captain Zima! We're done evacuating all villagers on the east side!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: North side villager evacuation complete!
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: West and south villagers are all evacuated too!
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: Got it. Mousse, you go double-check the headcount with the village chief. Then help them put out the fire. These villagers built their own houses, brick by brick, so every room you can save is a win.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: R—Roger!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Seanson, Lucci, with me. This next part of the job's gonna be tricky... We need to head into the storehouse, and get the medical supplies out.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: What? So they were in the village!
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Yeah... I'll tell you the whole story after we're done here.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But... you're telling me it's all in there? Captain, that's not a small fire.
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: I know, and this isn't an order.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: If you don't want to go, I'll go by myself.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Captain, this isn't a want-to-or-not kind of scenario...
attributes.name: Lucci

attributes.content: Dedushka, dedushka, will that bratan come back to help us?
attributes.name: Young Villager

attributes.content: In the spring, he said he'd return by autumn.
attributes.name: Young Villager

attributes.content: And then autumn came and he did, don't you remember? And he harvested the grains with us.
attributes.name: Young Villager

attributes.content: You silly little fool. That boy didn't say he'd come back in winter.
attributes.name: Old Villager

attributes.content: No, he said he'd come back the next time we're out of rye bread.
attributes.name: Young Villager

attributes.content: But—but...
attributes.name: Young Villager

attributes.content: ...Dedushka, weren't you just saying, we might not have bread to eat this winter?
attributes.name: Young Villager

attributes.content: So the bratan must be coming back soon!
attributes.name: Young Villager

attributes.content: *sigh*...
attributes.name: Old Villager

attributes.content: Come, sweet child. Be good now, your babushka is waiting for us over there.
attributes.name: Old Villager

attributes.content: Change of plans. We rescue the villagers' food first.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: B—But, Captain, given the situation, these villagers could well be in cahoots with Daniil!
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: They stole our stuff, and we're going to help them?
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: That's two different things... C'mon, you guys, with me.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: That's an order this time. And if we can't get the medical supplies thing squared off... I'll take the blame.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Say, how much grain do you figure could be left in there?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Given the present conflagration, the portion closest to the fire's origin is out of the question. Still, at least some of the outer portion should remain.
Hm? I don't think so~ There's still a chance for the inside part, it might just be a little overbaked!
After all that training, we finally get a shot at the real thing, huh? Move move move, girls, full steam ahead!
All else being equal, we've arrived in time. If we concert our efforts, perhaps we can still avert complete disaster.
Y—You guys...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: What are you doing here?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Back then...
You! You idiot... Do you even know what you've done?
It was an accident...
attributes.name: Sonya

attributes.content: Save it! Quickly, with the water! Bring the water!
It's no use! This little water's barely enough!
Th—The fire's spreading too fast!
Dammit... What are we waiting for, then?! Run!
N—No... This is our last reserve of food...!
attributes.name: Sonya

attributes.content: Forget her! Let's run!
Daniil left us a letter. He said you might need the USSG's help, Sonya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: After reading it, we went looking for Nearl. She told us the location of this village.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: That dumbass, Daniil...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Belay it, Sonya. No more hesitance.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: The five of us should be plenty! What about those two, though?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Er...
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: We'll go save the medical supplies!
attributes.name: Seanson

attributes.content: Everyone, let's do this! After we're done, I'll make super-tasty grenki for all of us!
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Sonya. Let's go together.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Anna, you absolutely didn't need to come.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: The USSG's already disbanded.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Yes, by your personal statement. Being the initial proponent of the Group's establishment, shouldn't you solicit my view?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Not to mention those of Lada, Rosalind, and Natalya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Okay, so what are your views?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: We all object.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I can more or less guess what your thinking ultimately was.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: To be honest, I've been deliberating over the USSG's continuation myself...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: If we never encountered Rhodes Island, our lives might now be much the same as Daniil's.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But you see, Sonya... even for all Rhodes Island gives us, it doesn't mean we must lose anything.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: We're not even in the same squad anymore.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Come, help me out.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: This bundle's quite the heavy load.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I'll carry this side. We need to hurry up.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Sonya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What is it?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: We may not be in the same squad anymore, true, and I estimate we'll only be further split up in future, but...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: At the very least, when you think to bear something alone, we'll come to your side like we are now...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Because we are eternal comrades.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Weird...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I can't believe the five of us are still together.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: And we're facing a fire, just like we did back then...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: If not for this fire...
No, there is no if.

attributes.text: Even if this fire is already lit...
Still we will link our hands, sing and skip.
Still we will lift the same food one and all.
The frozen earth will thaw to loose soil.
No longer will the seed cling to the seed's false name.
Once the winter night is through, she will spark tender, small blossoms.
